 M ay & Baker Nigeria Plc has appointed Senator Daisy Danjuma into the board of its directors.   A statement by the company explained that Danjuma had over 40 years experience in legal, administrative and public service.   Danjuma, who was a senator between 2003 and 2007 in Nigeria obtained a law degree from Ahmadu Bello University and was called to the Nigerian bar over 40 years ago.   She is an alumnus of the Lagos Business School, a member of the International Bar Association, the Nigerian Bar Association and the International Federation of Female Lawyers..   She had worked as a state counsel with the Lagos State Ministry of Justice in the office of the Director of Public Prosecutions.   Also,Â  Danjuma was a pioneer legal counsel to the Legal Aid Council (LAC).     She later worked as the company secretary/legal adviser to the Nigerian Television Authority between 1982 and 1992.   Danjuma is currently on the board of several companies. She was chairman board of directors, South Atlantic Petroleum Limited from 1999 to 2003 and is currently the executive vice chairman of the company.